    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="197" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <head>No. 142.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-09-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 22,
                                    1882</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 462.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 434, of the 30th ultimo, giving an account of your action
                            in relation to the cases of Mr. Meany and Mr. George, and in which is
                            inclosed a copy of your note to Lord Granville on the subject. Your
                            action is approved and your course in promptly protesting against the
                            treatment of these gentlemen is commended. The reply of Lord Granville
                            to your note is awaited with interest.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
